If the first character is a `%` character, the method checks the next character to determine whether a repeat count is specified. If the next character is a `*` character, the method sets the length to -1, which indicates a variable repeat count. If the next character is a digit, the method parses the digit sequence to determine the repeat count. The method continues to parse digits until it encounters a non-digit character.

