        throw new IllegalArgumentException("Matrix must be square");
    }

    if (rows == 1) {
        return matrix[0][0];
    }

    if (rows == 2) {
        return matrix[0][0]*matrix[1][1] - matrix[0][1]*matrix[1][0];
    }

    double det = 0;

    for (int j = 0; j < cols; j++) {
        det += Math.pow(-1, j) * matrix[0][j] * determinant(minor(matrix, 0, j));
    }

    return det;
}
```

The `cofactor` method takes a 2D `double` array `matrix` as input and returns a 2D `double` array containing the cofactors of each element of the input matrix. The `minor` method is a helper method that returns the minor of a matrix with respect to a specified row and column. The `determinant` method is another helper method that calculates the determinant of a matrix recursively.

