The `CombinedClassLoader` class is not part of the standard Java library, so it must be defined separately. Here is one possible implementation:

```
public class CombinedClassLoader extends ClassLoader {
    private ClassLoader[] loaders;

    public CombinedClassLoader(ClassLoader... loaders) {
        this.loaders = loaders;
    }

    @Override
    public Class<?> loadClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {
        for (ClassLoader loader : loaders) {
            try {
                return loader.loadClass(name);
            } catch (ClassNotFoundException e) {
                // Ignore and try next loader
            }
        }
        throw new ClassNotFoundException(name);
    }
}
```

This `CombinedClassLoader` attempts to load classes using each of the given classloaders in turn until it finds one that can load the class. If none of the loaders can load the class, then it throws a `ClassNotFoundException`.

