import java.security.cert.X509Certificate;
import java.util.regex.Matcher;
import java.util.regex.Pattern;

public static String getSecondarySubject(X509Certificate cert) {
    String primarySubject = cert.getSubjectX500Principal().getName();
    String organization = extractSubjectValue(primarySubject, "O");
    if (organization == null) {
        return ""; // primary subject is not an organization
    }
    String cn = extractSubjectValue(primarySubject, "CN");
    String ou = extractSubjectValue(primarySubject, "OU");
    if (ou != null && !ou.equals(organization)) {
        return ou; // OU is different from O
    }
    if (cn != null && !cn.equals(organization)) {
        return cn; // CN is different from O
    }
    return ""; // no secondary subject found
}

private static String extractSubjectValue(String subject, String key) {
    Pattern pattern = Pattern.compile(key + "=([^,]+)");
    Matcher matcher = pattern.matcher(subject);
    return matcher.find() ? matcher.group(1) : null;
}
```

The `getSecondarySubject` method first extracts the primary subject of the certificate as a string using the `getSubjectX500Principal()` method of `X509Certificate`. Then, it extracts the organization (O) field from the primary subject using the `extractSubjectValue` helper method, which uses a regular expression to match the key-value pair in the subject string. If the primary subject is not an organization, the method returns an empty string.

If the primary subject is an organization, the method checks if the certificate has a common name (CN) or organizational unit (OU) field that is different from the organization field. If so, it returns that field as the secondary subject. Otherwise, it returns an empty string.

Note that this method assumes that the certificate subject follows the X.500 naming convention, where each field is represented as a key-value pair separated by commas (e.g., "O=Acme, Inc., OU=IT, CN=www.example.com"). If the certificate subject is formatted differently, the method may not work correctly.

