    scriptSigStream.write(signature);

    // Push public key onto the stack
    scriptSigStream.write(publicKeyBytes.length);
    scriptSigStream.write(publicKeyBytes);

    // Convert scriptSig to byte array
    byte[] scriptSig = scriptSigStream.toByteArray();

    return scriptSig;
}
```

This method takes two parameters: `publicKeyBytes` and `signature`. `publicKeyBytes` is the byte array of the public key used to generate the pay-to-pubkey output. `signature` is the byte array of the signature generated by the private key corresponding to the public key.

The method first decodes the `publicKeyBytes` to get the `publicKey` object. It then verifies the `signature` using the `publicKey` and the actual message being signed.

Next, the method creates the scriptSig by pushing the `signature` and `publicKeyBytes` onto the stack. The scriptSig is then converted to a byte array and returned.

