public class Suspender {
    private int suspendCount;

    public synchronized void suspend() throws InterruptedException {
        suspendCount++;
        while (suspendCount > 0) {
            wait();
        }
    }

    public synchronized void resume() {
        if (suspendCount > 0) {
            suspendCount--;
            notify();
        }
    }
}
```

This `Suspender` class has two methods: `suspend()` and `resume()`. The `suspend()` method increments the `suspendCount` variable and then enters a `while` loop that waits until `suspendCount` is equal to 0. The `resume()` method checks if `suspendCount` is greater than 0, decrements it, and notifies any waiting threads.

