public void addJobsGroup(JobsGroup group) {
    synchronized (this) {
        // Check if there is a currently running group
        if (currentGroup != null) {
            // Wait for the currently running group to finish execution
            while (!currentGroup.isFinished()) {
                try {
                    wait();
                } catch (InterruptedException e) {
                    Thread.currentThread().interrupt();
                    return;
                }
            }
        }

        // Set the new group as the currently running group
        currentGroup = group;

        // Start executing jobs on the new group
        group.start();

        // Notify any waiting threads that the group has started execution
        notifyAll();
    }
}
```

Explanation:
- The method uses synchronization to ensure that multiple threads can't access the currentGroup variable at the same time.
- If there is a currently running group, the method waits until it finishes execution by calling `wait()` on the current thread. This allows the previous group to finish executing before starting the new group.
- Once the previous group has finished execution, the method sets the new group as the current group and starts executing jobs on that group.
- Finally, the method notifies any waiting threads that the new group has started execution by calling `notifyAll()`. This allows any threads waiting on the currentGroup variable to wake up and check if the current group has changed.

